Also, it is known that once given an initial time $\tau_0$, one can no longer use the $i\varepsilon$ terms to suppress the boundary terms in the UV. As a result, the tree level result depends on $\tau_0$ strongly and oscillations are present if the cutoff is sharp. Such dependence presents also for the BD initial condition. We show here that those $\tau_0$ dependent terms also decay with a similar exponent. In other words, the interactions practically serve as the $i\varepsilon$, and indeed pick up the physical initial state.

