\end{eqnarray}
where the $\tau^5$ terms are contributed by $e^{i(p+q-k)\Delta \tau}$, while $ \mathcal{O}(\tau^4)$ are contributed by other terms. In the sub-horizon limit, only $\tau^5$ terms are most relevant, so in the original expression, we only need to keep  $e^{i(p+q-k)\Delta \tau}$ like terms. In particular, in such case, all the related modes are BD modes.

